title: BBC Radio 4 - John Finnemore's Souvenir Programme - Series 1
description:
John Finnemore, writer and star of Cabin Pressure, regular guest on The Now Show and popper-up in things like Miranda and That Mitchell And Webb Look returns with half an hour of his own sketches, each funnier than the last.


1. Episode One (First Broadcast: Sun 18th September 2011)

John Finnemore, writer and star of Cabin Pressure returns to Radio 4 with half an hour of sketches. This week's show sees a big job, a small job, the career path of the average TV executive, and a tiger with a gun.

2. Episode Two (First Broadcast: Sun 25th September 2011)

John Finnemore reveals the truth behind the war effort (cats), sty construction, and evolution.

3. Episode Three (First Broadcast: Sun 2nd October 2011)

John Finnemore's show visits some documentary-makers, has a big debate, and then treats itself to a little trophy.

4. Episode Four (First Broadcast: Sun 9th October 2011)

John Finnemore's sketch show. Featuring some musical interludes from the zoo, and a sketch that only a fool would not find funny.
